content: Lots of info. Works just like it should. Can't wait for the app to evolve it only gets better from here.
replyContent: Thanks Paul, I'm definitely looking forward to getting my long list of new features added to the app in the coming months!

content: Good looking interface.  Awesome scorekeeping abilities.  Interfaces nicely to website.  Great way to find nearby courses.  I'd like to be able to update stuff about the website while still in the app though... for example, updating course conditions without going to the website
replyContent: Robert, to update conditions from the app, click the 3-dot menu while on a course page and choose "Update Course Conditions".  Thanks for getting the app, glad you like it!

content: All the features I need for an affordable price

I love the DGCourseReview website, so the app was a no-brainer. The app has a smart scoring interface that makes it easy to track the round without issue or confusion. The ability to upload to the site is great. Sometimes it's tough to find the courses when you don't have cell service, so it would be good to include the course listing in the download if possible. Would also be nice to have graphs that tie into statistics and a way to export all statistics to a file. I would recommend to a friend.
replyContent: Michael, courses are updated constantly on the site (and in turn, the app) so a downloadable course listing would be obsolete very quickly and would be massive given all the information the app has. As far as graphs and export functionality, they are available on the site in your scorebook.

content: This app is a great addition to their already awesome website.  I will likely be able to keep track of scoring in a much easier fashion, and even store them for referencing later.  I would recommend this to all of my DG friends!   Logging in with my site login was simple and worked first try.

HELP! Could not purchase this app. Google Play kept giving me the message that payment was declined. Tried Paypal, Credit Card and AT&T billing. Nothing worked. Could not get it to download to my LG phone. I got a message from AT&T thanking me for purchasing it and it STILL would not download. Now, in Google Play, it does not show INSTALLED. It just shows $4.99 in the green box. Frustrating!
replyContent:
James, you should contact Google support over this.  Here is a link to their help page: https://support.google.com/googleplay?hl=en#topic=3364260

Click the "Contact Us" link on the upper right, then "Android Apps & Games", "Problem buying or downloading" and you can chat with someone at Google that will hopefully get this sorted out for you.

content: Very useful, some of the stores listing are out of date but hasn't impacted me so far as I know the spots in my area anyhow.  The course locator feature has been useful when deciding what to play next.
replyContent: Anthony, First off, thanks so much for getting the app. I really appreciate it! If you notice a store on the list that has been closed (or if you don't see your local shop) please contact me via the site (Contact Us link) and I'll remove and/or add the shop(s).  Thanks again!

content: Doesn't really offer anything that a browser doesn't. Best part is having the hole length at hand, but that's easy enough to look up as well. It also looks extremely outdated, like it was designed for Android 2.1. They really didn't follow any Material Design guidelines.
replyContent: I'm really sorry you feel that way Shane.  The app does let you record scores and upload them directly to the site, sync your scores between devices, etc.  Plus there is the smoothness of a native experience versus a stateless web page. And we have more features planned for the future so hopefully you can revisit your review then.

content: I recently played a course where there were a few par 4s that were listed in the app as 3 and I couldn't change it. It would be perfect if you could change the par depending on the pin position on the fly.
replyContent: Matthew, that feature and a lot more are coming in a future update.  I have tons of cool additions planned :) In the mean time, if the pars are off you can fix them on the site and the change will be reflected within the app.

content: Love the site and app. I use them all the time. Best resource for discin'!
Course locater, score card, local tournaments, nearby stores, connection to the most comprehensive Disc Golf website on the internet, all in a convenient, simple package. What more could you want.

However I uninstalled for the refund because I found another with most courses mapped, and the option to add multiple players without requiring a separate log in. I prefer the simplicity of this app over the other, and it's those two features that convinced me to choose the other; both are paid applications.
replyContent: Tim, I'd say at least 90% of the courses have one or more maps on DGCR. They are located under Links/Files on the course screen (shortcut from the in-round menu as well).  Also, players can be added without a site login, that is optional if you'd like to send your rounds to the site, maintain course lists, etc.

content: I've used a bunch of different apps for scorekeeping, but the DGCR app has everything I need and a lot I never realized I needed but now can't live without.  All the course reviews that you enjoy at the website are there, along with directions and course maps (where they've been uploaded).  Course pictures and everything  - all there.  And the scorecard!  Upload to your DGCR account automatically after each round, track your stats, everything.  Yeah, it costs money, but the good stuff in life usually does, and the DGCR app is worth it.
Love the app, best one out there for the price. I'm running the new M developer preview and app won't open. I'm sure this will probably be fixed when M is released.
replyContent: Jacob, Glad you like the app! I think the M Developer Preview was just released, I'm not sure my developer even has a handset to test that on yet.  But rest assured, by the time M is actually out the app will be working on it.

content: Course locator is great combined with phone gps is very quick and convenient. I can't find a quick score option. It currently only lets you score one hole at a time. Also when I import my rounds from the dgcr site it only imports three rounds. Any advice? UPDATE: Thanks for fast feedback on no quick rounds. Quick round records are my majority use of site. This ap allows you to dynamically record a scorecard as you play but a quickround function would be nice as well. Definitely worth the money thanks again.
replyContent: Nathaniel, the app doesn't allow quick rounds and doesn't import them. If most of your rounds are quick that's the deal. If that isn't the case please email me with your username on the site and I'll take a look to see what's up.

content: If you are a stat junkie, this is for you. Blends perfectly with the website. One request: on the fly hole averages

Made the account and fix my local park info on the website, and the app still register the old data. Once this works then I'll change my rating.                                      ** I end up clearing the cache, logged in again and it was updated. **
replyContent:
Nickolas, 

The app caches course data for around 24 hours. If you want to update faster than that look up the course and choose "Refresh Course Info" in the 3-dot menu.

content: Score-keeping app that syncs with the best course information and let's you backup your (and your friends') scores online... That's all I wanted and that's what this is.  Considering the amount of free info available on the website, the small app fee is nothing.  Something I was unsure of until I got the app; A paid premium web account is not required to use this app and backup online, you only need that if you want in depth score analysis or "courses not played" search capability.

I've used every DG app published, and the DGCR app is the finest. The course database integration is top notch. The feedback I've submitted to the publisher has been patched very quickly. The app performs as expected and has sane defaults that are intuitive. Rounds submitted to DGCR become part of the stats report for analysis. The use interface is simple and quick, I can enter 4 scores in seconds while walking between holes. This app is 5 stars today and it continues to get better.
This app is super simple to use! Favorite app I have used.
Mountain Crest,  Las vegas is my home course and the scoring needs to be edited. It be nice if we could edit the scoring.
replyContent: John, Can you please email me and tell me what you mean by "edit the scoring"?  If you're referring to the course information, please visit dgcoursereview.com, login and you can update or add any information or photos for your local course(s) and it will be reflected in the app immediately. If you want to email me the changes, I can do them for you

content: My only gripe is that tee and pin positions are both listed as tee positions. Having those separate and adjustable for individual holes would be great. I play some courses where I play long tees except for a few holes; however, if the pins are at a shorter position, the app still thinks I'm playing long since I've selected long tees for the entire course. Looking forward to future updates!
replyContent: Andrew, Right now locals will (ideally) update the current pin positions on the site when they change (it's a matter of clicking a few radio buttons) and that's reflected in the app automatically. I realize that won't always happen though so choosing a pin on the fly is something I'm planning on adding in a future update.

content: Nice clean recording app. Love the course maps and info. All the information from the site, but in a nice format. I only gave three stars because the price was a little off setting.

I'm a fan of the DGCR website, and I'm an even bigger fan of this app. I've bought many of the other disc golf apps, but I've put them all away in favor of this one. I''m a keeper of stats, and this app allows me to easily upload rounds to DGCR and to sync the stats on my phone with those on the website. As a scorekeeper this app has one of the most usable and customizable interfaces I've seen. It's easy to see in bright light, and entering scores is push-button easy. I also appreciate the app's links to the DGCR website's great catalog of courses and course information. This makes finding and navigating to courses in unfamiliar areas a snap. One shortcoming with the scorekeeper is that you can't automatically select a starting hole other than #1, but the manual workaround is practically painless, and I understand this feature should be added in the future.

Does what you want a scorecard to do as well as update to your website profile. Sync all feature doesn't seem to work for me or maybe I'm just reading it wrong. Have to manually upload each round individually which isn't so bad. Looking forward to updates (shotgun start, uploading rounds from other apps)
replyContent: I'm going to rename "Sync All" back to "Import All", I didn't realize it was confusing, sorry about that! You can pick and choose which rounds you want to upload to the site (skip the bad ones! :D). You have to import rounds from other apps through the site. There's a link at the bottom of your scorebook. If you don't see your app, please email me.

content: Really enjoying this app for recording rounds. Keep the updates coming! I'd like to see an interface that allows the scorekeeper to submit other dgcr members rounds to their online profile for review without requiring other players to log in on some else's device. Also it'd be nice be able to start a round on a course from the course overview. Once you've searched for the course and found it, just hit 'start new round' and it jumps to the scorecard creation page. Thanks, and keep it up!

I have paid for and downloaded several DG apps and this is the best one of all.  As a DGCR user, it syncs my scores, it allows me to find courses on the road and it is very intuitive.  I am sure as time passes there will be even more to recommend for this application.  Great work.
If you love the DGCR web site and wanted an easy to use and accurate scoring app that syncs with the web page, then you are in luck.

I would love this app more it it would allow me to pick which hole I'm starting on. Some days I'll only play the back 9 at my local course and cannot figure out how to do that. If its in there please let me know, if not please add a hole started on option, this would also help with shotgun start league rounds.
replyContent:
Brian,

Starting hole will be added in an upcoming update along with a bunch of other stuff to flesh out the scoring functionality.  For now, you could swipe over to the starting hole in the hole bar and tap it to skip right to that hole. Then when you get to 18 "finish" the round if you're only doing 9 or swipe back to #1 and go from there.

content: Best disc golf score app

Does everything you need it to do. I wish that you didn't have to input other players credentials into your local device as opposed to looking them up and they authorize your updates after a round. Hopefully in a future update.  EDIT:  Thanks for the response from the dev.  Makes sense! 5 stars
replyContent:
Drew,

Any credentials saved on the device are encrypted, no plain text passwords for the device owner or any other player are ever saved to the phone.  I opted to do it that way so someone couldn't be a jerk to random people and just fill up their mobile queues on the site with bogus rounds.

content: Very very helpful in finding courses especially when your traveling.  Love the scorekeeper to.  Excellent App.
Love the round ratings. Really need to add the option to make a new DGCR account from the app itself.
Been using it every time I play. Any bugs I've encountered have been fixed quickly. Keep up the good work guys!
replyContent: Thanks Eric! Definitely working hard to fix any issues that come up and then we can start doing some exciting things, like adding some new features to the app!

content: Of course I haven't taken it out into the course yet... But it has almost everything I'd want, plus stuff I didn't know I did. And looks way nicer than the Google Sheet scorecard I made.
This is the one you are looking for if you travel at all.  If you don't it is a great scoring app.
Works great up until it crashes and loses your running score. Back to paper and pencil.
replyContent:
Andy, 

The issues you were encountering should be fixed in v1.11.  Please update your app and give it a try.

content: Being used to a competitor's app for a while, this lacks some features that I really enjoy. That said, if this had been around two years ago, this would've received 5 stars because I wouldn't know what it's missing. Tim does seem very responsive to requests (though the response may be that that's not something being planned currently or is a long-term plan). Just since the initial release, the app has come far. For the next few outings, I'll be using both apps. This has great potential!

Had a few bugs when I initially installed it but they have have been fixed. The website has been my go to for years, awesome to have the app. (Edited after developer reply, even support is obviously great)
replyContent: Conditions updates are already in there.  Just go to the course screen and you'll find the option to update course conditions in the 3-dot menu on the upper right.

content: I've used other apps for keep score for years now and liked this right away.  Easy to use and gives you more options to change how the app keeps score while being user friendly.  Thanks!  The course finder, shop finder, and tourney finder are nice too.  Edit: I suggested the following not too long ago and the change was made! Thanks!    "My only suggestion is the screen where you look at the score at the end of a round would be better if it had the course played listed as well as the tees played. Our club uploads tag rounds on facebook to update tags and that info would be nice when we take a screen cap and post it."

Finding a course is easier than ever with one tap. I feel like I could go on and on about how great this app is for disc golf. Needless to say, but a few bucks for this = well worth it! One question, does the amount of putts alter a rating? Say if I get a three on all holes but two putt everything rather then get a three on all holes  and one putt everything?
replyContent:
Rob, 

Glad you like the app and thanks for getting it! To answer your question, no, the # of putts does not effect your round rating or player rating. It's just a stat you can track if you choose to.

content: I entered the score for all 18 holes, finished the game, checked out the final scorecard and everything looked good.  Later, it discarded all the scores except for holes 1 - 3.  How hard is it to keep track of 18 values?  The rest of the app is decent, though not without faults.  For example, sometimes nearby courses don't show on the map.  Frankly, I expected more from an app that costs this much
replyContent:
Andrew,

The issues you were encountering and more should be fixed in v1.11. Please update your app and give it a try. If you want to email me about the nearby courses thing you mentioned I'll definitely have the developer look into it.

content: This is the only app you need to find, travel to, keep score, and check your stats, for disc golf. Used it today and it will be the only one I use from now on. Great job guys.

I've gone through almost all of the disc golf scoring apps on the market, and the DGCR app is an early contender for best scoring app. With access to the largest DG course directory in the world and synchronization with the foremost scorebook, DGCR separates itself from the competition. With the responsiveness of timg and the development team, this app can only get better!
Design is super functional. Pretty flaw free for recently released.  Awesome support and app keeps getting better.

Great features, but one letdown, I was using it as a scorecard but it erased scores between holes and I would turn my phone screen off. Big Letdown, but the course finder and statistic keepers are awesome for me.
replyContent:
Brian,

The issues you were encountering and a lot more should be fixed in v1.11. Please update your app and give it a try.  I apologize for the issue and hopefully this takes care of it for you!

content: I was using easyscorecard which is good, but no longer supported. This app's trump card is that it is now possible for everyone in the foursome to have the round synced (uploaded to DGCR, and downloaded to their own devices) after the round, even if they weren't the scorekeeper!  Everyone just has to be a registered member of DGCR (free) and have the app ($5).  I think Udisc pro is the only other app that offers this functionality, and only for ios right now, and that is a recurring $4 annual fee. The DGCR website is my go to website for off the course info, so this was a no brainer for me.  Based on the sites membership size and the proprietors dedication, I expect solid support moving forward, and the app to only get better than what is already an awesome disc golf app.
This dedicated app integrates really well with the website and Google Maps to make searching for courses a breeze. It proved rather handy on my recent road trip.

Have been using this app for a bit now, and have to say out of all of them for the Android, this is the one to use.  Tim actually looks over reviews and takes users opinions in the account for future upgrades and updates, the whole team works closely with the community to ensure the app keeps growing and getting better as it goes.
Great app
Would like to see list of played courses more organized and smaller. Would like to have that easier to manage. I'm more interested in that feature and it feels clumsy. Otherwise great
replyContent:
Garrett,

If you haven't already, please hop on the forum or email us suggestions on how we could improve that feature and what you were looking/hoping for.

content: What more do you need? Score keeping that links to online profile for stats and analysis. Detailed information on courses.  Easy to use.  Worth the price.

I recently downloaded the app and am enjoying it more than EasyScoreCard Pro. It's very easy to use. Also, the ability to filter courses played out straight from the app is an extremely cool feature for dgcr premium members. I definitely recommend it. It's worth the $5 for sure.

I have been using the mobile website on my phone for years and this is a big upgrade! The interfaces for finding and getting information on courses are great. Plus this app got me to use my phone for score keeping for the first time.
Nice clean interface. I have used every disc golf app that is out. Both free and nonfree and dgcr is the best for straight up score card, course info and ease of use.

Everything is great but I did have one issue. I accidentally backed out of my score during a round after replying to a text and I couldn't get back to my current round! Had to find my scorecard, read all my scores to a friend then re-enter my scores. Definitely needs an obvious and quick option to jump back in to round in session. If there is already an option, please share. Literally only problem so far. Thanks. UPDATE:  When I used this app last week I couldn't get back in my game.  I just looked today, and now you can! Very easy and obvious. Good job to DGCR. They are on it. Love the app. 5 stars, easily if you are in to DG.
replyContent: Thanks Jeff! Version 1.03 removes the back button at the top of the round screen and disables the back button on the phone while on that screen.  That should help avoid accidentally going back for you and others in the future.

content: App does everything it should.  I like being able to search for courses based on GPS and finding disc retailers that way is a very nice feature too.  Score keeping functionality is good.  I like that it reorders players based on last hole score and that it gives you the option to record OB strokes and number of putts.  Feature request:  the ability to mark a course as played from the app would be nice.
replyContent: Thanks for the great review! You actually can already do that.  Tap the "3 dot" menu while looking at a course and the "Mark as Played" option is right there.  Tapping that marks the course within the app and on the site.

content: Excellent scorecard app.  Does everything my prior app did and then some.
Yup
DGCR, one of the best go-to web sites for disc golf, nailed this app right down the fairway! Extremely user friendly with an easy to use interface.

EDITED- from 2 stars to 4 stars. Found my played course list but still not 5 stars as it looks like you need to be premium site member to import you stats?  Editing again: 4 to 5 stars because while the app is new and not perfect, DGCR is obviously committed to making it the best DG app available. Kudos DGCR!
replyContent: Glad you got the played course list figured out and thanks for updating your review! The next update will remove the premium requirement to import rounds from the site and fix a few other things people found.  Should hopefully be out next week.

content: Love the functionality so far. I haven't played a round yet but the search and course page interaction is awesome. I am looking forward to trying it during a round.     !Need to be able to review my profile better. Can't see my courses, or am I missing it?
replyContent: When you click "Played Courses" to start a round, the app will download all your courses from the site.  It doesn't do it automatically when you first enter your info since some people have like 500+ courses to download which could take a while.

content: Extremely clean, Very easy to navigate. Best Disc Golf app out there!
Makes life that much easier!
Love the app and Timg on DGCR is really accessible for suggestions.

Especially if you like to log your scores in! Great way to support the website. No IAPs or subscriptions and includes future updates. Smooth operation on my Nexus 6. Finding local courses and shops works the way it should.
I LOVE the ease to view pictures. I'm visual when it comes to new courses/holes and it's very seemless to view them. Amazing!
Everything you need for a dg adventure across the state or a quick casual round. Great app from a great website.
With a variety of tools that interact with DGCR's rich course database, this app is going to be hard to beat.
Works, search feature s could be made more friendly. Maps are solid though.  Bout time tim!

I've been playing with a beta of this app for a few weeks and it looks awesome,  is super clean and easy to use and takes everything you love about the live site and shares it in the ease of an app.  If you don't have this on the course your bag is incomplete.
I know it was designed for phones but on the big screen of a Tab S it looks fantastic -  Aisling13
